.TH "pci_epf_alloc_space" 9 "pci_epf_alloc_space" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
pci_epf_alloc_space \- allocate memory for the PCI EPF register space
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void *" pci_epf_alloc_space
.BI "(struct pci_epf *epf "  ","
.BI "size_t size "  ","
.BI "enum pci_barno bar "  ","
.BI "size_t align "  ","
.BI "enum pci_epc_interface_type type "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "epf" 12
the EPF device to whom allocate the memory
.IP "size" 12
the size of the memory that has to be allocated
.IP "bar" 12
the BAR number corresponding to the allocated register space
.IP "align" 12
alignment size for the allocation region
.IP "type" 12
Identifies if the allocation is for primary EPC or secondary EPC
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Invoke to allocate memory for the PCI EPF register space.
